{
  "answer": "**The ghazal is Mirza Ghalib's \"baazeecha-e-atfaal hai duniya mere aage\" (*Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 213).**[^1]\n\nThe first couplet, dismissing the throne of Solomon and the Savior's miracle, reads:  \n*\"The fabled throne of Solomon is but a piece of play,*  \n*The Savior's miracle, a word I brush away.\"*[^2]\n\nThe separate couplet on Faith and Heresy reads:  \n*\"My Faith holds back, while Heresy would have its way;*  \n*The Kaaba's at my back, the Church is on display.\"*[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/#p-411662).\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/#p-dfc2f3).",
